examples: The bombed bridge was left unsupported and soon collapsed.

definitions.definition: For which support or help is not available.
examples: This obsolete software is unsupported . Please upgrade to the latest version.

definitions.definition: Without confirmation from a credible source, without verifying support
examples: The sentence was unsupported by an inline citation or general bibliographic reference source notes.

definitions.definition: Not supported by or borne out of evidence or facts.
